with outstanding performers receiving better pay than those with 
mediocre skills or past their prime 
the states decision to give up its monopoly over the arts has 
drawn some criticism in the official press with artists being 
quoted as saying many traditional chinese and minority musical 
dance and opera troupes are doomed by the survival of the 
fittest policy 
