born chesney baker in yale okla in 1929 the musician set the 
standard for what jazz buffs knew as the cool school 
in 1952 he was working with charlie parker on the west coast 
when he joined the pianoless quartet of british saxophonist gerry 
mulligan 
with his good looks and youth and fragile introverted tone 
baker soon became a cult figure in 1953 he topped the metronome 
trumpet poll and started his own quartet his work became more 
assured and outgoing 
baker looked something like actor james dean and sounded 
something like famed jazz trumpeter bix beiderbecke as a player 
miles davis was his main inspiration 
in 1955 baker took a group to europe that showed high promise 
then his career started to suffer an italian court sentenced him 
to a 16month prison term in 1960 for drug possession 
in san francisco in 1968 baker said he was beaten up by 
hoodlums and suffered severe injuries that included the loss of his 
teeth a trumpet players nightmare 
for two years baker didnt play but he said recently he had 
quit drugs he began recording again and made an album with pop 
star elvis costello 
