sir kamisese mara in april elections 
after the coup an interim government was set up but when it 
didnt please rabuka he staged a second takeover on sept 25 
since then a nervous calm has settled over fiji the countrys 
touristbased economy is in shambles 
gross domestic product is down 11 percent sugar production 
the countrys major cash crop is down 203 percent tourism has 
plummeted 269 percent and the fiji dollar has been devalued by 33 
percent 
at his home in viseisei western fiji bavadra issued a 
statement vowing to continue to push for racial equality in fiji a 
group of 300 islands east of australia 
