a light plane crashed between two 
apartment buildings just after takeoff saturday leaving three 
people dead and another critically injured police said 
the plane carrying four people crashed about five blocks east 
of middlesborobell county airport according to wfxy radio newsman 
jim gilbert who was on the scene moments after the crash 
there were no reports of casualties on the ground police said 
benny collins a commercial photographer said the planes 
engine was sputtering as it tried to gain altitude collins said 
the plane banked as if to return to the airport but fell and hit a 
guy wire on a utility pole 
he said the plane plowed into the ground between two small 
apartment buildings but did not catch fire 
gilbert said power lines were downed and aviation fuel was 
