the state court of appeals on a defense request to throw out the 
indictment if they fail there defense attorneys plan to go to the 
state supreme court 
if there is no delay jury selection is scheduled to begin 
thursday 
in insisting that he broke no laws mecham has advanced several 
arguments 
that the october 1986 loan was actually reported properly 
because it was lumped with other funds and listed as a 465000 
loan from mecham to his campaign the funds were lumped together as 
a timesaving matter mecham said 
that the failure to report the loan was an honest mistake 
by willard mecham who filled out the financial reports the best 
he knew how 
that mecham is the victim of selective prosecution because 
other public officials have amended their reports without facing 
criminal charges 
that in any case whether the loan was properly reported or 
not there was no criminal intent to hide it 
the prosecution however is expected to point to a letter from 
mecham to wolfson in which he promised the loan would remain 
confidential another key piece of evidence is a november 1986 
receipt that showed a 350000 contribution to the campaign from 
mecham although he acknowledged he made no such contribution 
none of the attorneys involved prosecutors barnett lotstein 
and michael cudahy mecham defense lawyer michael scott and 
willards attorney joe keilp is tipping his hand on trial 
strategy 
but among the witnesses expected to be called are a number of 
